Reposting for feedback

>https://archiveofourown.org/works/43701771

Hey guys It's me, AP. Been a while since I've said anything, but I'm here now to post a new story that I've been working on: Of Crimson Scales. First chapter is ~9,500 words

Do read the story's summary on Ao3 if you're interested, but this is a story that takes place in an alternate universe that I've been developing. (Basically our world but with dragons and other things inspirited by biblical lore and folklore.) It takes place after the Carolingian empire was divided up and follows the son of a Duke and the task set before him. I'm trying to be vague, but there is a dragoness involved that may or may not have crimson scales.

As always, I appreciate any and all feedback. Constructive, or not.

I'm basically taking a short break from VNFF to work on this story. Been working on slice of life viper stories for a year and a half, and I wanted to mix it up. Had a bunch of ideas for dragon stories floating around in my head and I wanted to get a few concept chapters for this idea down on "paper". Once I get there, I'm going back to working on VNFF.
